|title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL1097634W The Mirror and the Lamp]
|passage=He was thinking; but the glory of the song, the swell from the great organ, the clustered '''lights''', [&hellip;], the height and vastness of this noble fane, its antiquity and its strengthâ€”all these things seemed to have their part as causes of the thrilling emotion that accompanied his thoughts.}}
